    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-08T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-08T09:00:00-05:00" n="200"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d200">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">103.9169/7–845: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 200 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chief of the Mission for Economic Affairs in the United
                        Kingdom</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BTC1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Blaisdell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Assistant Secretary of State</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_CWL1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clayton</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d200fn1">Sent to the Acting Secretary of State
                        over the signature of <persName corresp="#p_WJG2">Winant</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent—<gloss target="#t_Niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-08T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >July 8, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6878. From <persName corresp="#p_BTC1">Blaisdell</persName> for <persName
                        corresp="#p_CWL1">Clayton</persName>.</p>
                <p>After careful consideration and consultation with <gloss target="#t_Amb1"
                        >Amb</gloss>
                    <persName corresp="#p_WJG2">Winant</persName>, we believe that Soviet Govt
                    should be informed that US intends to raise questions at Berlin Conference
                    concerning organization for production and distribution of German coal on open
                    account as indicated in <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>’s 5415.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d200fn2">
                        <ref target="#d426">Document No. 426</ref>.</note> We feel it would be more
                    effective for <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> to notify Soviet Govt from
                    Washington where agenda for Berlin Conference has been formulated than through
                    Embassies in London.<note n="3" xml:id="d200fn3">See <ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv02#d1040">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>,
                            document No. 1040</ref>.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
